New Records: Zimbabwe moved to the top of Group J with five points after their 1-0 victory over Namibia
Key Match Events: The match's only goal came from a penalty by Khama Billiat after Jordan Zemura was fouled
Post-Match Reflections: The match was played behind closed doors, and Zimbabwe's victory moved them to the top of the group standings
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played at Orlando Stadium in Johannesburg due to both teams' stadiums being condemned
Others: The return fixture against Namibia is expected to attract a larger crowd
